JOHANNESBURG - The Zulu Royal Family will address members of the media at 4 pm on Sunday to provide details of the plans for the week of mourning, as declared by the KwaZulu-Natal provincial government. This as the nation prepares to plant King Goodwill Zwelithini keBhekuzulu on Wednesday night. The planting will be followed by a memorial service on Thursday.  Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android device.